SQUIBS Update Example

Week of 12/3/2023 - Week of 12/10/2023

Cumulative Sample Summary

Number of weeks sampled: 33

Number of samples received: 65

Number of samples processed: 65

Number of individual squid processed to date: 8077

News/comments:

  • A SQUIBS sampling demonstration was given to students from the Knauss Fellowship program on 12/8.

  • At least 2 samples expected for Week of 12/17, one from area 6A and one from 6B.

  • One hermaphroditic organism was found in a sample from 5Zw during week 40 (Week of Oct 1). It was found to have a fully-developed testis, spermatophores, and accessory glands, but no nidamental gland or ovary. Its parameter values were recorded but have been excluded from the generation of the cumulative data figures. The organism is currently preserved in the freezer at the Narragansett Lab.

Map

Reference map of potential collection locations. This project uses NAFO Regulatory Areas as a point of reference from which to target fishing trips, in an effort to collect squid samples throughout a representative spatial range of the fishery.
